      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, i tried the margin-bottom but it didnt really touch the problem. the overlap is still happening like the title is just sitting right on top of the image.\n\ni also noticed that sometimes when i refresh the page on mobile, the elements jump around for a second before they settle. is that a layout shift issue or something else? im worried the container isnt actually respecting the flex direction on smaller screens.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's possible that with the very narrow margins, the text and image are intersecting. Let me correct this by introducing padding instead of margin so that there's a buffer around the image, and let's size the image appropriately within the container:\n\n```css\n@media screen and (max-width: 749px) {\n  .product__info-container {\n    padding: 10px;\n  }\n  .product__image {\n    margin-bottom: 20px; /* Increased spacings around the image */\n    max-width: 100%; /* Optional, to ensure the image is responsive */\n  }\n}\n```\nAlso, for the layout shift, it sounds like your elements are not stable. This can be caused by flexible widths, like percentages or other CSS properties that change based on the viewport. Make sure all elements are either setting a max-width or have a width in a fixed unit, rather than being completely responsive. Check if you have any ems, %s or viewport units (vw, vh) against fixed units (px).\n\n\nTo ensure the flex container is functioning correctly, we should check if `.product__info-container` directly contains the image, title and price or if they're being nested in another container that might be interfering. If necessary",
      "source": "target",
